input_str: DETROIT, MI - It wasn't easy, but the Detroit City Council got it done. Tuesday's unanimous decision from the City Council to approve zoning changes for the planned $650 million Detroit Red Wings arena and entertainment district was months in the making. Approval came with a few disclaimers. Though all council members present (councilman Scott Benson was absent) voted in favor of rezoning the 12-acre, nearly-vacant plot of land
